modules.description: Parses bytecode from an input channel, invoking user-provided callbacks for different sections such as code, data, symbols, and primitives. It processes the bytecode structure, extracting and dispatching each part to the corresponding handler if provided. Useful for analyzing or transforming OCaml bytecode during compilation or debugging tasks.

Parses OCaml bytecode from an input channel, invoking user-defined callbacks for sections like code, data, symbols, and primitives. Works directly with input channels and bytecode structures, enabling analysis or transformation of bytecode during compilation or debugging. Useful for tools that need to inspect or modify bytecode, such as profilers, optimizers, or custom loaders.
